XXIX. 12. Q. Metellus Pius, son of Metellus Numidicus, was praetor in 87 Rc. and distinguished himself by his services in the Social war ; was instrumental in procuring the election of Calidius to the praetorship. As proconsul in Spain he conducted the war against Sertorius for eight years and was awarded a triumph at its close in 72, so that at the time of Calidius’ impeachment he must have been absent from Rome3 cf. infra si Romae esse potuisset.
